965494 224 Prohibition of structures or fixtures which cause obstruction in street.
1833319 1No person shall, except with the permission of the Chairperson granted in this behalf, erect or set up any wall, fence, rail, post, step, booth or other structure whether fixed or movable or whether of a permanent or temporary nature, or any fixture in or upon any street or upon or over any open channel, drain, well or tank in any street so as to form an obstruction to, or an encroachment upon, or a projection over, or to occupy any portion of such street, channel, drain, well or tank.
384702 2Nothing in this section shall apply to any erection or thing to which clause (c) of sub- section (1) of section 229 applies.
295925 225 Prohibition of deposit, etc., of things in streets.
616429 1No person shall, except with the permission of the Chairperson and on payment of such fee as he in each case thinks fit, place or deposit upon any street, or upon any open channel, drain or well in any street or upon any public place any stall, chair, bench, box, ladder, bale, or other thing whatsoever so as to form an obstruction thereto or encroachment thereon.
512047 2Nothing in sub- section (1) applies to building material.
561772 226 Power to remove anything deposited or exposed for sale in contravention of this Act. The Chairperson may, without notice, cause to be removed--
439783 aany stall, chair, bench, box, ladder, bale, or other thing whatsoever, placed, deposited, projected, attached or suspended in, upon, from or to any place in contravention of this Act.
128817 bany article whatsoever hawked or exposed for sale on any public street or in other public place in contravention of this Act and any vehicle, package, box or any other thing in or on which such article is placed.
520344 227 Prohibition of the tethering of animals and milking of cattle.
1245575 1No person shall tether any animal or cause or permit the same to be tethered in any public street or public place.
971245 2No person shall milk or cause or permit to be milked any cow or buffalo in any street or public place.
1285120 3Any animal tethered or any cow or buffalo found being milked as aforesaid in any street may be removed by the Chairperson or any municipal officer or employee and be impounded and dealt with under the provisions of the Cattle- trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871). Provision concerning execution of works in or near to streets
1165775 228 Precautions during repair of streets.
1905056 1The Chairperson shall, so far as is practicable, during the construction or repair of any public street, or any municipal drain or any premises vested in the Council--
1862619 acause the same to be fenced and guarded,
1536785 btake proper precautions against accident by shoring up and protecting the adjoining buildings,
879243 ccause such bars, chains or posts to be fixed across or in any street in which any such work of construction or repair is under execution as are necessary in order to prevent the passage of vehicles or animals and avert danger.
1018043 2The Chairperson shall cause such street, drain or premises to be sufficiently lighted or guarded during night while under construction or repair.
74
1168583 3The Chairperson shall, with all reasonable speed, cause the said work to be completed, the ground to be filled in, the street, drain or premises to be repaired and the rubbish occasioned thereby to be removed.
26746 4No person shall, without the permission of the Chairperson or other lawful authority, remove any bar, chain, post or shorting, timber, or remove or extinguish any light set up under this section.
422588 229 Streets not to be opened or broken up and building materials not to be deposited thereon without permission.
980700 1No person other than the Chairperson or a municipal officer or other municipal employee shall, without the written permission of the Chairperson--
570019 aopen, break up, displace, take up or make any alteration in, or cause any injury to the soil or pavement or any wall, fence, post, chain or other materials or thing forming part of any street; or
85173 bdeposit any building materials in any street; or
608113 cset up in any street any scaffold or any temporary erection for the purpose of any work whatever, or any posts, bars, rails, boards or other things by way of an enclosure, for the purpose of making mortar or depositing bricks, lime, rubbish or other materials.
375856 2Any permission granted under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub- section (1) shall be terminable at the discretion of the Chairperson on his giving not less than twenty- four hours' notice of such termination to the person to whom such permission was granted.
1687789 3The Chairperson may, without notice, cause to be removed any of the things referred to in clause (b) of sub- section (1) which has been deposited or set up in any street without the permission specified in that sub- section or which having been deposited or set up with such permission has not been removed within the period specified in the notice issued under sub- section (2): Provided that nothing in this sub- section shall apply to cases under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub- section (1) in which an application for permission has been made with such fee as may be prescribed by the Chairperson in this behalf but no reply has been sent to the applicant within seven days from the date of the application.
1671147 230 Disposal of things removed under this Chapter.
155331 1Any of the things caused to be removed by the Chairperson under this Chapter shall, unless the owner thereof turns up to take back such thing and pays to the Chairperson the charges for the removal and storage of such thing, be disposed of by the Chairperson by public auction or in such other manner and within such time as the Chairperson thinks fit.
98767 2The charges for removal and storage and sale of the thing sold under sub- section (1) shall be paid out of the proceeds of the sale thereof and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the thing sold on a claim being made therefor within a period of one year from the date of sale, and if no such claim is made within the said period, shall be credited to the New Delhi Municipal Fund. Naming and numbering of streets and numbering of buildings
392114 231 Naming and numbering of streets.
1723227 1The Chairperson may--
337097 awith the sanction of the Council determine the name or number by which any street or public place vested in the Council shall be known;
75
1996610 bcause to be put up or painted at a conspicuous part of any building, wall or place at or near each end, corner or entrance of such street or on some convenient part of such street, the name or number by which it is to be known;
1326944 ccause to be put up or painted on boards of suitable size the name of any public place vested in the Council;
803043 ddetermine the number or sub- number by which any premises or part of such premises shall be known and cause such number or sub- number to be fixed to the side or outer door of such premises or to some place at the entrance of the enclosure thereof.
886077 2No person shall destroy, remove, deface or in any way injure or alter any such name or number or sub- number or put up or paint any name or number or sub- number different from that put up or painted by order of the Chairperson. Repair or enclosure of dangerous places
951627 232 Chairperson to take steps for repairing or enclosing dangerous places.
278680 1If any place is, in the opinion of the Chairperson, for want of sufficient repair or protection or enclosure, or owing to some work being carried on thereupon, dangerous or causing inconvenience to passengers along a street or to other persons including the owner or occupier of the said place, who have legal access thereto or to the neighbourhood thereof, the Chairperson may by notice in writing require the owner or occupier of such place to repair, protect or enclose the same or take such other step as shall appear to the Chairperson necessary in order to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising therefrom.
281156 2The Chairperson may before giving any such notice or before the period of any such notice has expired, take such temporary measures as he thinks fit to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising therefrom; and any expense incurred by the Chairperson in taking such temporary measures shall be recoverable from the owner or occupier of the place as an arrear of tax under this Act. Lighting of streets
1981305 233 Measures for lighting. The Chairperson shall--
760479 atake measures for lighting in a suitable manner all such public streets and public places as may be specified by him;
1169002 bprocure, erect and maintain such number of lamps, lamp posts and other appurtenances as may be necessary for the said purpose;
181767 ccause such lamps to be lighted by means of oil, electricity or such other light as he may determine.
1078158 234 Prohibition of removal, etc., of lamps.
734696 1No person shall, without lawful authority, take away or wilfully or negligently break or throw down or damage--
789832 aany lamp or any appurtenance of any lamp or lamp post or lamp iron set up; in any public street or any public place;
29172 bany electric wire for lighting such lamp;
1986377 cany post, pole, standard, stay, strut, bracket or other contrivance for carrying, suspending or supporting any electric wire or lamp.
707208 2No person shall wilfully or negligently extinguish the light of any lamp set up in any public street or any public place.
1597288 3If any person wilfully or through negligence or accident breaks, or causes any damage to any of the things described in sub- section (1), he shall in addition to any penalty to which he may be subjected under this Act, pay the expenses of repairing the damage so done by him.
